history.content: Taking the class right now -- seems like you mostly get an overview of the current problems in computational genomics research and some of the tools that are used (hidden Markov models, convolutional neural networks, and other machine learning tools) while learning to read research papers in the field. Your grade is mostly presentation/project based, as there are no exams currently planned for the class. Seems like many weeks will be listening to and discussing other student's presentations on key papers in the field, so it's more research-oriented than your typical undergrad CS course.
